observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:
a. Expedite the implementation of the projects and activities stated on its SWMP to ensure the protection of public health and the environment;
b. Direct the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board to review and update the CY 2018-2027 Ten-Year SWM Plan of the Municipality in compliance with Section 12 of RA No. 9003 to ensure its sustainability and viability in relation to the local developments in the solid waste management of the Municipality.

We recommended that Management:
a. Require the Municipal Treasurer – GSO Designate and the Municipal Accountant to update their records and ensure that Property records are reconciled with the Accounting records;
b. Direct the Municipal Accountant to record in the General Fund books the completed projects under the Trust Fund aggregating ₱1,199,218.33;
c. Direct the Inventory Committee to regularly conduct a physical count of PPEs and to properly classify the PPE items in the RPCPPE to facilitate the reconciliation of the results of the count with the Treasury and Accounting records; and
d. Conduct a one-time cleansing of the PPE accounts of the Municipality in accordance with the guidelines and procedures set under COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 to come up with reliable PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition, and accountability.

We recommended and management agreed to the following:

To restore to the DRRMF the amount of P84,400.00 to be taken from the General Fund through a supplemental budget to be enacted in CY 2017;

b. The MDRRMO to strictly observe the guidelines set forth in the utilization of the DRRMF and to properly determine the projects and activities that should be appropriately charged to the fund.
